{"lemma":"مِشْكَواتُ","slug":"مِشْكَواتُ","root":"ش.ك.#","root_slug":"ش-ك-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ك-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مِشْكاة","root":"شكو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22891"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%B4%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"niche for lamp","examples":[{"text":"مَثَلُ نُورِهِ كَمِشْكَاةٍ فِيهَا مِصْبَاحٌ","english":"The likeness of his light is like a niche with a lamp in it."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived by Nöldeke from Ge'ez መስኮት (mäskot), መሥኮት (mäśkot)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22891","headword_ar":"مِشْكَاةٌ","root":"$kw and $kY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A niche in a wall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hollow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuw~apN","text_ar":"كُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a wall, not extending through;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, M, K, &c.;) in which a lamp, placed therein, gives more light than it does elsewhere: thus expl: by the generality of the expositors [of the Kur-án]; and this is said by Ibn-' Ateeyeh to be the most correct explanation: (TA:) said by Aboo-Moosà to mean the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"iron,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaden, thing in which is the wick"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the lamp"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: thought by Az to mean the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tube which is the place of the wick in the glass lamp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuw~ap","text_ar":"كُوَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is thus called: (TA:) some expl. it as having this meaning in the Kur xxiv. 35, and say that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miSobaAH","text_ar":"مِصْبَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"there mentioned is the lighted wick: (Bd:) accord. to Mujáhid, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pillar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEamuwd","text_ar":"العَمُود"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the top,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head, of which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miSobaAH","text_ar":"مِصْبَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lamp"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is put:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"iron things by means of which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qinodiyl","text_ar":"قِنْدِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lamp"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is suspended:"},{"kind":"text","text":"IJ says that its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", and hence it is [often] written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi$ok`wpN","text_ar":"مِشْكٰوةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and Zj says that it is an Abyssinian word, and used in the language of the Arabs: (TA:) [the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAkK","text_ar":"مَشَاكٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAHK","text_ar":"مَسَاحٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misoHaApN","text_ar":"مِسْحَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] Kaab says that, in the verse of the Kur [xxiv. 35], by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi$okaAp","text_ar":"مِشْكَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant the breast of Mohammad; and by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miSobaAH","text_ar":"مِصْبَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":", his tongue; and by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zujaAjap","text_ar":"زُجَاجَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", his mouth. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Bd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}